   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>CHAPTER TWO THE REGENERATED SPIRIT</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>OF THE BELIEVERS Scripture Reading: Gen 2:7; 2 Cor 5:17; Eph 3:16; 2:1, 5-6; John 3:5-6; 1 Pet 1:3; John 3:36a; Gal 2:20a; Eph 2:22; 3:16b-17a; John 14:23b; 4:24; Rom 1:9; 8:16; 2 Tim 4:22; Eph 1:17; 3:5; Rev 1:10; 4:2; 17:3; 21:10; Eph 4:23; 5:18; 1 Cor 6:17 OUTLINE In God's old creation the spirit of man is the reality of man and not the person of man Gen 2:7.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>In God's new creation the spirit of the believers is the person of the man of the new creation the inner man of the believers 2 Cor 5:17; Eph 3:16: Being dead in sins Eph 2:1.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>Being revived and made alive through the resurrection of Christ Eph 2:5.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>And being enlivened and regenerated with the life of God by the life-giving Spirit in Christ's resurrection Eph 2:6; John 3:5-6; 1 Pet 1:3.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>The regenerated spirit of the believers has: The life of God as the second life, the new life, of the believers John 3:36a.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>Christ as the embodiment of the Triune God, the Father, Son, and Spirit, living in the believers to be the person of the believers as the new creation Gal 2:20a.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>The regenerated spirit of the believers becomes the dwelling place of the processed and consummated Triune God in them Eph 2:22 , and it also becomes their inner man Eph 3:16b , in which Christ as the embodiment of the Triune God dwells 2 Tim 4:22 and from which He spreads to make His home in their heart Eph 3:17a ; this is the processed and consummated Triune God's making an abode in the believers John 14:23b .</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>The regenerated spirit of the believers becomes the organ for them to worship, serve, receive, possess, experience, and enjoy God John 4:24; Rom 1:9; 8:16; 2 Tim 4:22.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>The regenerated spirit of the believers is also the organ for them to receive God's wisdom, revelation, and vision Eph 1:17; 3:5; Rev 1:10; 4:2; 17:3; 21:10.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>The regenerated spirit of the believers spreads into their mind to become the renewing spirit in their mind Eph 4:23.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>The regenerated spirit of the believers is being filled with God Eph 5:18.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>The regenerated spirit of the believers and the consummated Spirit of God are mingled as one spirit 1 Cor 6:17.</S>
   </TEXT>
